habitat_description: This species is only described from the outflows of Barton Springs in the city of Austin in Travis County, Texas (Hillis et al. 2001; Lannoo 2005; Green et al. 2013). This is considered a subterranean species related to Texas blind salamanders (E. rathbuni) and Blanco blind salamanders (E. robusta) from San Marcos in Hays County, Texas (Hillis et al. 2001). Adults have only been reported from spring outflows in caves.
